    Modified the LPC status reporting to make it clearer.␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀    Connection_retry value.@␀␀␀␀    errors.  The numbers of times a job is retried is set by the␀␀␀C␀␀␀␀    Fixed Send_job() to make it more robust in the face of protocol␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀    capability.D␀␀␀␀    Modified the top level Makefile to use the GNU Make -C directory␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀    make all␀␀␀<␀␀␀␀    cp configure $DEST; cd $DEST; configure --srcdir=$SRC; \␀␀␀$␀␀␀␀    cd LPRng.<version>; SRC=`pwd`; \␀␀␀=␀␀␀␀    compile the LPRng software in another directory by using:␀␀<␀␀␀␀    more than one level of directory structure.  You can now␀␀␀>␀␀␀␀    this fixes a bug with the autoconf code that cannot handle␀A␀␀␀␀    Moved all of the configuration information to the root level;␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀C␀␀␀␀    Added better tests for sys_errlist and sys_siglist definitions.␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀    is added.␀␀B␀␀␀␀    but will require updates to the Makefile if a new library file␀D␀␀␀␀    library file order.  This provides a simple form of portability,␀␀␀?␀␀␀␀    Removed the 'lorder/tsort' from Makefile, and hardcoded the␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀?␀␀␀␀    TCP write operation, and do not look for the \n terminator.?␀␀␀␀    of LPD code expect the command lines to be sent as a singleC␀␀␀␀    a single write where possible.  Apparently some implementationsA␀␀␀␀    several writes to send a line;  this has been modified to use␀␀?␀␀␀␀    In link_support.c/Link_send(),  the original code was using␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀    Makefiles... sigh...␀␀␀D␀␀␀␀    Changed the Makefile 'TARGET' name to avoid conflicts with other␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀+␀␀␀␀Mon Jul 24 09:29:15 PDT 1995 Patrick Powell␀␀␀␀Release LPRng 1Alpha7␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀M␀␀␀␀    where writes are done have been surrounded by Set_timeout, Clear_timeout.␀␀O␀␀␀␀    routines.  These assume that writes will be done with timeouts;  all placesS␀␀␀␀    (Write_fd_str(), Write_fd_len()),  and timeout (Set_timeout(), Clear_timeout())L␀␀␀␀    have guessed at this interaction?  Created a couple of utility functions␀␀␀N␀␀␀␀    Fixed up a whole minor mess of writes and timeout interactions.  Who would␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀4␀␀␀␀    dependency,  but who cares, as long as it works.␀␀␀J␀␀␀␀    can be run from another directory.  This is very very strange autoconf␀N␀␀␀␀    man/Makefile and src/Makefile modified to use INCLUDE=.. so that configure␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀N␀␀␀␀    Fixed up the configure.in file to use the old dnl, socket, etc. libraries.␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀    etc. etc.␀␀E␀␀␀␀    when a code checkout program was run: if/then not being executed,␀␀G␀␀␀␀    Several rather silly coding errors in various places that turned up␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀$␀␀␀␀    redirect            printer@host␀␀␀␀␀␀␀    printing_disabled   1␀␀)␀␀␀␀    of entries for future expansion, i.e.␀␀E␀␀␀␀    now the spool control file can have any number of different types␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀ ␀   @
  ␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀"#''''''''''''''''x'p'h'`'X'P'H'@'8'0'(' ''''␀'&&&%%%%%%%%%%%x%p%h%`%X%P%H%@%8%0%(% %%%%␀%$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$x$p$h$`$X$P$H$@$8$0$($ $$$$␀$#######%&&&&&&&&&&&&&x&p&h&`&X&P&H&@&8&0&(& &&&&␀&%%%%




p
 

