.  I wish there was a way to read the man pages and␀␀␀@␀␀␀␀  I have modified configure so that it checks for 'fd_set' being␀␀␀9␀␀␀␀  on HPUX and other systems now have 'fd_set' data types.␀␀B␀␀␀␀  Based on third hand reports, some installations of GNU compilers␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀H␀␀␀␀ (Spotted by the eagle eyes of: Eric S. Raymond <esr@golux.thyrsus.com>)␀␀␀␀␀␀␀  man page fixes.␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀3␀␀␀␀Version LPRng-3.8.14 - Tue Aug  6 09:14:06 PDT 2002␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀    before?8␀␀␀␀    when I looked at it... I wonder why I did not see it␀␀␀9␀␀␀␀    This removes a race condition.  It was bloody obvious␀␀:␀␀␀␀    for the data files if the ERROR or DONE flags are set.␀9␀␀␀␀    it checks to see if there is an error and only checks␀␀6␀␀␀␀    - checks to see if the INCOMING flag is set BEFORE␀␀␀␀␀  Remove_done_jobs␀␀␀␀␀  ␀3␀␀␀␀Version LPRng-3.8.15 - Sun Aug 11 13:11:48 PDT 2002␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀.␀␀␀␀  to get a better print spooler or whatever...␀:␀␀␀␀  sit in an endless loop.  No solution for this one except␀7␀␀␀␀  keep trying to send jobs even when they get error and4␀␀␀␀  left in the queue as errors.  Note - spoolers will␀␀␀9␀␀␀␀  Bad incoming jobs are removed.  You do not get the jobs␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀;␀␀␀␀   (From the wish list of: Rick Cochran <rcc2@cornell.edu>)D␀␀␀␀  configure --disable-werror removes the -Werror option from CFLAGS.␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀3␀␀␀␀   (Suggested by:  Rick Cochran <rcc2@cornell.edu>)␀␀␀␀  before you send it.␀␀8␀␀␀␀  lpr now honors :mx=xx values so you can check job size␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀3␀␀␀␀Version LPRng-3.8.16 - Mon Aug 12 15:26:05 PDT 2002␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀2␀␀␀␀   find id' as the job hold file has been removed.␀8␀␀␀␀   But you might get a bogus error message about 'cannot␀␀␀7␀␀␀␀   the job would get moved or removed anyways.  Sigh...@␀␀␀␀   an LPC action on a job.  After a bit of thought, decided that␀␀␀>␀␀␀␀   that would cause LPD to stop printing if you removed or did␀D␀␀␀␀  Found a race condition between LPD printing, LPRM, and LPC actions␀␀␀3␀␀␀␀Version LPRng-3.8.17 - Sat Oct 26 20:11:28 PDT 20