: wo7␀␀␀␀␀␀  Added Yet Another LPRng Option: user_is_authuser␀␀␀␀␀␀ L5␀␀␀␀␀␀    (Patch by: Stepan Kasal <kasal@math.cas.cz>)dw=␀␀␀␀␀␀  lpd.conf did not have 'include' functionality working. L␀␀␀␀␀␀an1␀␀␀␀␀␀  and signing certs are in the right places. pK␀␀␀␀␀␀  certificate, even though one has been requested and the certificatesG␀␀␀␀␀␀  signed by non-root CA indicates that the client is not sending aJ␀␀␀␀␀␀  the truly complicated details.  Note that testing with certificateshF␀␀␀␀␀␀  Added SSL authentication.  See the README.SSL.SECURITY file for ␀␀␀␀␀␀ t<␀␀␀␀␀␀  (Problem noticed by: Rick Cochran <rcc2@cornell.edu>) anD␀␀␀␀␀␀  lpr Kerberos authentication failures were not being reported.wor␀␀␀␀␀␀rl␀␀␀␀␀␀  <kasal@math.cas.cz>)B␀␀␀␀~␀␀  Typo's in documentation corrected.  (Patch by: Stepan Kasal␀␀␀␀␀}␀␀F␀<␀␀␀␀|␀␀  the PRINTCAP_ENTRY environment variables for filters.endE␀␀␀␀{␀␀  client.xxx and server.xxx values.  They are also propagated tockG␀␀␀␀z␀␀  The lpc client and lpc server commands will display the selected␀␀␀␀y␀␀ v␀␀␀␀x␀␀  it.)H␀␀␀␀w␀␀  imagine a use for this,  but it is there if somebody wants to useervI␀␀␀␀v␀␀  file, allowing global overrides for clients and servers.  (I can't,␀F␀␀␀␀u␀␀  This selection operation also works with values in the lpd.conf␀␀␀␀␀t␀␀ I␀␀␀␀s␀␀     :lp=%P@destinationa r␀␀␀␀r␀␀    lp:server␀1␀␀␀␀q␀␀     :lp=%P@server.hostname:force_localhost@ p␀␀␀␀p␀␀    lp:clientt␀␀␀␀o␀␀,␀␀␀␀␀n␀␀  flags, as shown below:ceJ␀␀␀␀m␀␀  This is equivalent to and replaces the :client and :server printcapv␀␀␀␀l␀␀ t#␀␀␀␀k␀␀     :server.lp=%P@destination␀␀␀␀j␀␀ # specified destinationueA␀␀␀␀i␀␀ # used by lpd server # the server will now send jobs to the s1␀␀␀␀h␀␀     :lp=%P@server.hostname:force_localhost@nd␀␀␀␀g␀␀ server␀␀␀<␀␀␀␀f␀␀ # used by clients, forcess them to send to # specified a ␀␀␀␀e␀␀    lp:,␀␀␀␀␀d␀␀  Example of use:n␀␀␀␀c␀␀st␀␀␀␀b␀␀  to another lpd queue.␀␀␀G␀␀␀␀a␀␀  in situations where the lpd server is forwarding or sending jobsH␀␀␀␀`␀␀  entry to be used for both client and server operation, especially NoD␀␀␀␀_␀␀  The purpose of this enhancement is to allow a single printcapa r␀␀␀␀^␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀]␀␀    (client)   xxx = vvv␀␀G␀␀␀␀\␀␀    lpd (server)          xxx = vvv client.xxx = vvv    lpr,lpq...H␀␀␀␀[␀␀    Entry               Program Type          Sets server.xxx = vvv  u␀␀␀␀Z␀␀e ␀␀␀␀Y␀␀  etc.G␀␀␀␀X␀␀  lpd server or the LPRng client programs lpr, lpq, lprm, checkpc,H␀␀␀␀W␀␀  corresponding xxx variable when the printcap entry is used by theto␀@␀␀␀␀V␀␀  client.xxx or server.xxx then this can be used to set the␀␀␀D␀␀␀␀U␀␀  facility.  Briefly,  if you have a printcap entry of the form␀␀␀H␀␀␀␀T␀␀  After much consideration, added the 'client.xxx' and 'server.xxx',␀D␀␀␀␀S␀␀  Major Enhancement In Printcap and Configuration Functionality,␀␀␀␀␀R␀␀eu8␀␀␀␀Q␀␀Version LPRng-3.8.13 - Mon Jul 22 09:07:57 PDT 2002,␀␀␀␀␀P␀␀␀␀A␀␀␀␀O␀␀   (Suggested by: Jim Van Sickler <vansickj-eodc@Kaman.com>) l-␀␀␀␀N␀␀  command = /usr/local/sbin/lpc start %p,␀C␀␀␀␀M␀␀  queuepause command = /usr/local/sbin/lpc stop %p queueresume
