euid() missing␀J␀␀␀␀    Filters: CTI-ifhp-1.1.1 lp-pipe-1.0.0  lp-support-1.0.0 psfilter-1.0.2␀-␀␀␀␀    Documentation - DOC/Intro and DOC/Install␀␀␀␀␀␀Release LPRng 1-2-0␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀D␀␀␀␀    i.e. - if you have CONTROL permission you also can remove files.␀␀␀D␀␀␀␀    messages.  Added CONTROL permission checking for LPRM operation;␀␀␀@␀␀␀␀     fixes in portable.h Fixed lpr, lprm MAN pages;  fixed usage␀␀␀@␀␀␀␀    hagberg@mail.med.cornell.edu (Eric Hagberg) A/UX portability␀␀␀(␀␀␀␀     uninitialized in Get_queue_remove()␀␀␀C␀␀␀␀     - common/getqueue.c off by one error - LPD/lpd_remove.c - cfpp7␀␀␀␀     initialization in LPD/lpd_jobs.c, LPD/lpd_status.c>␀␀␀␀     - fixed an erroneous test in checkremote.c - missing data␀@␀␀␀␀    Martin Forssen: maf@dtek.chalmers.se or maf@math.chalmers.se␀␀␀␀␀␀␀Release LPRng 1-2-1␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀    is done.␀␀␀E␀␀␀␀    introduced to handle this.  By default, no file or device locking␀␀C␀␀␀␀    algorithmically.  An new printcap flag 'lk' (lock LP device) isC␀␀␀␀    combinations of files, devices, etc., are too much to deal withA␀␀␀␀    This is only a problem in pr_support.c;  the permutations and␀␀C␀␀␀␀    allow file locking only if the files are opened R/W, no APPEND.G␀␀␀␀    implementing portable file locking.  It turns out that some systemsB␀␀␀␀    This sounds ridiculous,  but there is yet ANOTHER problem with␀␀␀␀␀Release LPRng 1-2-2␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀7␀␀␀␀    printcap - added 'qq' (save queue name in job file)G␀␀␀␀    SVR4 - added sys/systeminfo.h, sysinfo() call replace gethostinfo()+␀␀␀␀    miscellaneous errors reported by users.6␀␀␀␀    common/jobcontrol.c - erroneous error field update␀4␀␀␀␀    Fixed lprm -a flag;  documentation error as well␀␀␀␀␀␀␀Release LPRng 1-2-3␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀      in separate directories.␀?␀␀␀␀    Makefile.in - removed ${SRC}/src, etc. to allow compilation5␀␀␀␀      - removed O_NDELAY from various open statements␀␀,␀␀␀␀    curt@ltpmail.gsfc.nasa.gov (Curt Tilmes)␀␀␀␀␀␀␀      redefinition problems.␀␀␀J␀␀␀␀      terminfo.h include file so you can include it multiple times without␀J␀␀␀␀      but not terminfo.h and termcap.h.  I recommend putting guards in the␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀asier.

    Added bk-of-filter-options and bk-filter-options to provide compatibility
    with old style filters.

    Fixed up a lot of minor portability issues with Solaris2.4, using the
    SUN Soft C compiler.  Fixed fumble in gethostinfo.c - will die if
    it cannot find the local host name; this is very bad and should be
    immediately fatal instead of dying later.

    Fixup the the TESTSUPPORT/Makefile to be a little more intelligent.
    Also, put in guards to make sure that you have GNU Make.  This appears
    to be essential for sanity reasons alone.

Release LPRng 1Alpha5
Mon Jul 17 10:57:49 PDT 1995 Patrick Powell

    ********* BSDI *************
    Literally hundreds of questionable items were reviewed, fixed
    or modified.  The 'snprintf' function was renamed to 'plp_snprintf'
********* BSDI *************␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀+␀␀␀␀Mon Jul 17 10:57:49 PDT 1995 Patrick Powell␀␀␀␀Release LPRng 1Alpha5␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀-␀␀␀␀    to be essential for sanity reasons alone.␀␀J␀␀␀␀    Also, put in guards to make sure that you have GNU Make.  This appears␀G␀␀␀␀    Fixup the the TESTSUPPORT/Makefile to be a little more intelligent.␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀-␀␀␀␀    immediately fatal instead of dying later.␀␀F␀␀␀␀    it cannot find the local host name; this is very bad and should be␀E␀␀␀␀    SUN Soft C compiler.  Fixed fumble in gethostinfo.c - will die if␀␀I␀␀␀␀    Fixed up a lot of minor portability issues with Solaris2.4, using the␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀    with old style filters.M␀␀␀␀    Added bk-of-filter-options and bk-filter-options to provide compatibility␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀:␀␀␀␀    server.  This allows debugging of filters much easier.␀G␀␀␀␀    Added -Pprinter option to LPD to simply start and run a spool queue␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀    about the printer status.␀␀F␀␀␀␀    Modified the format for LPQ status information,  added more detail␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀    safe or appear to be safe.␀G␀␀␀␀    Considered using safestrcmp() for this reason; checked most places;H␀␀␀␀    Fixed a missing check for null string with STRCMP in src/getqueue.c.␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀J␀␀␀␀    Clean up some code in printcap.h, printcap.c, lp_config.h, getconfig.cd␀␀␀␀␀ati?␀␀␀␀    Editted MAN pages heavily in light of comments from people.$␀␀␀␀      is put in the MAN page source.␀␀␀F␀␀␀␀    Update man pages.  Fix up installation so that VERSION information␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀,␀␀␀␀    Fixed up some minor 'lint' level errors.␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀    put them in src/default.c␀␀D␀␀␀␀    Separated out default printcap and configuration initialization,␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀    recursion.␀G␀␀␀␀    level of the distribution.  Added top level MAKEFILE with directoryD␀␀␀␀    Reorganized the auto configuration code so that it is at the top␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀+␀␀␀␀Thu Jul 20 19:23:03 PDT 1995 Patrick Powell␀␀␀␀Release LPRng 1Alpha6␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀&␀␀␀␀    Removed a redundant error message.␀9␀␀␀␀    Modified the LPC status reporting to make it clearer.␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀    Connection_retry value.@␀␀␀␀    errors.  The numbers of times a job is retried is set by the␀␀␀C␀␀␀␀    Fixed Send_job() to make it more robust in the face of protocol␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀    capability.D␀␀␀␀    Modified the top level Makefile to use the GNU Make -C directory␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀    make all␀␀␀<␀␀␀␀    cp configure $DEST; cd $DEST; configure --srcdir=$SRC; \␀␀␀$␀␀␀␀    cd LPRng.<version>; SRC=`pwd`; \␀␀␀=␀␀␀␀    compile the LPRng software in another directory by using:␀␀<␀␀␀␀    more than one level of directory structure.  You can now␀␀␀>␀␀␀␀    this fixes a bug with the autoconf code that cannot handle␀A␀␀␀␀    Moved all of the configuration information to the root level;␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀C␀␀␀␀    Added better tests for sys_errlist and sys_siglist definitions.␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀    is added.␀␀B␀␀␀␀    but will require updates to the Makefile if a new library file␀D␀␀␀␀    library file order.  This provides a simple form of portability,␀␀␀?␀␀␀␀    Removed the 'lorder/tsort' from Makefile, and hardcoded the␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀?␀␀␀␀    TCP write operation, and do not look for the \n terminator.?␀␀␀␀    of LPD code expect the command lines to be sent as a singleC␀␀␀␀    a single write where possible.  Apparently some implementationsA␀␀␀␀    several writes to send a line;  this has been modified to use␀␀?␀␀␀␀    In link_support.c/Link_send(),  the original code was using␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀    Makefiles... sigh...␀␀␀D␀␀␀␀    Changed the Makefile 'TARGET' name to avoid conflicts with other␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀+␀␀␀␀Mon Jul 24 09:29:15 PDT 1995 Patrick Powell␀␀␀␀Release LPRng 1Alpha7␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀M␀␀␀␀    where writes are done have been surrounded by Set_timeout, Clear_timeout.␀␀O␀␀␀␀    routines.  These assume that writes will be done with timeouts;  all placesS␀␀␀␀    (Write_fd_str(), Write_fd_len()),  and timeout (Set_timeout(), Clear_timeout())L␀␀␀␀    have guessed at this interaction?  Created a couple of utility functions␀␀␀N␀␀␀␀    Fixed up a whole minor mess of writes and timeout interactions.  Who would␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀4␀␀␀␀    dependency,  but who cares, as long as it works.␀␀␀J␀␀␀␀    can be run from another directory.  This is very very strange autoconf␀N␀␀␀␀    man/Makefile and src/Makefile modified to use INCLUDE=.. so that configure␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀N␀␀␀␀    Fixed up the configure.in file to use the old dnl, socket, etc. libraries.␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀    etc. etc.␀␀E␀␀␀␀    when a code checkout program was run: if/then not being executed,␀␀G␀␀␀␀    Several rather silly coding errors in various places that turned up␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀$␀␀␀␀    redirect            printer@host␀␀␀␀␀␀␀    printing_disabled   1␀␀)␀␀␀␀    of entries for future expansion, i.e.␀␀E␀␀␀␀    now the spool control file can have any number of different types␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀ ␀   @
  ␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀"#''''''''''''''''x'p'h'`'X'P'H'@'8'0'(' ''''␀'&&&%%%%%%%%%%%x%p%h%`%X%P%H%@%8%0%(% %%%%␀%$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$x$p$h$`$X$P$H$@$8$0$($ $$$$␀$#######%&&&&&&&&&&&&&x&p&h&`&X&P&H&@&8&0&(& &&&&␀&%%%%




p
 

